This Agreement may be terminated by either party at their discretion, provided that such termination occurs upon the happening of any of the following events:

1. Material breach by the other party which remains uncured for a period of 30 days after written notice thereof is given;
2. Insolvency or bankruptcy proceedings being commenced against either party;
3. The dissolution or winding up of either party;
4. A change in control or ownership of either party resulting in a material alteration to their business operations or the Agreement's terms; or
5. Any other event that materially and adversely affects either party's ability to perform its obligations under this Agreement, as determined by the non-breaching party in its sole discretion.

In such cases, the terminating party shall provide written notice of termination to the other party, and the Agreement shall be deemed terminated effective immediately or on a mutually agreed date. Upon termination, the parties shall promptly settle all outstanding obligations and return any property belonging to the other party.
